1 (2) “Facilities” means hospitals and related institutions whose rates have
2 been approved by the Commission.
3 (b) The Commission shall assess and collect user fees on facilities as defined in
4 this section.
5 (c) (1) The total fees assessed by the Commission may not exceed the greater
6 of:
7 (i) 0.1% of the immediately preceding fiscal year’s budgeted,
8 regulated, gross hospital revenue; or
9 (ii) The largest amount determined under this paragraph for a fiscal
10 year during the immediately preceding 5 fiscal years.
11 (2) The total user fees assessed by the Commission may not exceed the
12 Special Fund appropriation for the Commission by more than 20%.
13 (3) The user fees assessed by the Commission shall be used exclusively to
14 cover the actual documented direct costs of fulfilling the statutory and regulatory duties of
15 the Commission in accordance with the provisions of this subtitle and any administrative
16 costs for services to the Commission provided by the Department.
17 (4) The Commission shall pay all funds collected from fees assessed in
18 accordance with this section into the Health Services Cost Review Commission Fund.
19 (5) The user fees assessed by the Commission may be expended only for
20 purposes authorized by the provisions of this subtitle.
21 (6) The amount specified in paragraph (1) of this subsection limits only the
22 total user fees the Commission may assess in a fiscal year.
